{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Touch.rotationAngle","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/rotationAngle","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch_events\">Touch events</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch\"><code>Touch</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/Touch\"><code>Touch()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/clientX\"><code>clientX</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/clientY\"><code>clientY</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/force\"><code>force</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/identifier\"><code>identifier</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/pageX\"><code>pageX</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/pageY\"><code>pageY</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/radiusX\"><code>radiusX</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/radiusY\"><code>radiusY</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><em><code>rotationAngle</code></em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/screenX\"><code>screenX</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/screenY\"><code>screenY</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/target\"><code>target</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Touch Events</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TouchEvent\"><code>TouchEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TouchList\"><code>TouchList</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"summary","title":"Summary","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Returns the rotation angle, in degrees, of the contact area ellipse defined by <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/radiusX\"><code>Touch.radiusX</code></a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/radiusY\"><code>Touch.radiusY</code></a>. The value may be between 0 and 90. Together, these three values describe an ellipse that approximates the size and shape of the area of contact between the user and the screen. This may be a relatively large ellipse representing the contact between a fingertip and the screen or a small area representing the tip of a stylus, for example.</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect1\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> This attribute has <em>not</em> been formally standardized. It is specified in the <a href=\"https://w3c.github.io/touch-events/\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" title=\"The 'Touch Events – Level 2' specification\" rel=\" noopener\">Touch Events – Level 2</a> <span class=\"spec-draft\">Draft</span> specification and not in <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/touch-events/\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" title=\"The 'Touch Events' specification\" rel=\" noopener\">Touch Events</a> <span class=\"spec-rec\">Recommendation</span>. This attribute is not widely implemented.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> angle <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> touchItem<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>rotationAngle<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"angle\"><code>angle</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The number of degrees of rotation to apply to the described ellipse to align with the contact area between the user and the touch surface.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example","title":"Example","isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/radiusX#example\">Touch.radiusX example</a> includes an example of this property's usage.</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/touch-events/#dom-touch-rotationangle","title":"Touch Events"}],"query":"api.Touch.rotationAngle"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.Touch.rotationAngle","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Touch/rotationAngle/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Summary","id":"summary"},{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Example","id":"example"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"Returns the rotation angle, in degrees, of the contact area ellipse defined by Touch.radiusX and Touch.radiusY. The value may be between 0 and 90. Together, these three values describe an ellipse that approximates the size and shape of the area of contact between the user and the screen. This may be a relatively large ellipse representing the contact between a fingertip and the screen or a small area representing the tip of a stylus, for example.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-02-18T09:26:54.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Touc